# Flutter — FVM with Pinned Version

The `device_apps` Flutter project uses [FVM](https://fvm.app/) with a pinned Flutter version defined in `device_apps/.fvmrc`.

**Pinned version: Flutter 3.41.4 / Dart 3.11.1**

## Always use `fvm flutter` for commands

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
fvm flutter pub get
fvm flutter pub upgrade
fvm flutter analyze
fvm flutter build apk
fvm flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs

# ❌ BAD — uses global Flutter, which may be a different version
flutter pub get
dart pub get
```

## Package dependency compatibility

When adding or upgrading any Flutter/Dart package:

1. Verify the package supports **Dart SDK ≥ 3.11.1** and **Flutter ≥ 3.41.4** before adding it
2. If a package requires a newer Flutter/Dart SDK than pinned, do NOT upgrade — find an earlier compatible version instead
3. The `environment.sdk` in `pubspec.yaml` is pinned to `^3.11.1` — do not raise this without also updating `.fvmrc`

## Updating the pinned version

If a Flutter SDK upgrade is needed:
1. Update `device_apps/.fvmrc` with the new version
2. Update `device_apps/pubspec.yaml` `environment.sdk` to match the new Dart SDK
3. Run `fvm install` then `fvm flutter pub get`
4. Update this rule and `mintdocs/build/flutter-app.mdx` to reflect the new version
